  16. (** Helpers for Intel code generators *)

  18. (* The DSL* modules expose functions to emit x86/x86_64 instructions
  19.    using a syntax close to AT&T (in particular, arguments are reversed compared
  20.    to the official Intel syntax).

  22.    Some notes:

  24.      - Unary floating point instructions such as fadd/fmul/fstp/fld/etc.
  25.        come with a single version supporting both the single and double
  26.        precision instructions.  (As with Intel syntax.)

  28.      - A legacy bug in GAS:
  29.    https://sourceware.org/binutils/docs-2.22/as/i386_002dBugs.html#i386_002dBugs
  30.        is not replicated here.  It is managed by X86_gas.
  31. *)
